This paper deals with the complexity and immunity of P-selective sets, which are closely related to computational complexity theory and algorithmic randomness. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also involves information theory and cryptography, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
